Two men were arrested in connection with house robbery in Worcester, Western Cape police said on Thursday. Police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk, said on Wednesday, at about 10.30am, police responded to a house robbery incident at Bergsig and arrested two Zimbabwean nationals who were allegedly involved in the incident. It is alleged that the two men, aged 38 and 40, threatened the owner of the house with a firearm to open the house. The suspects took her cellular telephone and an undisclosed amount of cash and fled the scene, after which they were arrested and the stolen goods recovered, Van Wyk said. Both men are expected to appear at Worcester Magistrates Court on Friday, on a charge of robbery. African News Agency For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.